18    /**
19    * An annotation description describes {@link java.lang.annotation.Annotation} meta data of a class without this class
20    * being required to be loaded. All values of an annotation are therefore represented in unloaded state:
21    * <ul>
22    * <li>{@link java.lang.Class} instances are represented as {@link TypeDescription}s.</li>
23    * <li>{@link java.lang.Enum} instances are represented as
24    * {@link net.bytebuddy.description.enumeration.EnumerationDescription}s.</li>
25    * <li>{@link java.lang.annotation.Annotation}s are described as
26    * {@link AnnotationDescription}s.</li>
27    * <li>All primitive types are represented as their wrapper types.</li>
28    * </ul>
29    * An annotation can however be loaded in order to access unwrapped values. This will cause a loading of the classes
30    * of these values.
31    */

131    /**
132    * A loaded variant of an {@link AnnotationValue}. While
133    * implementations of this value are required to be processed successfully by a
134    * {@link java.lang.ClassLoader} they might still be unresolved. Typical errors on loading an annotation
135    * value are:
136    * <ul>
137    * <li>{@link java.lang.annotation.IncompleteAnnotationException}: An annotation does not define a value
138    * even though no default value for a property is provided.</li>
139    * <li>{@link java.lang.EnumConstantNotPresentException}: An annotation defines an unknown value for
140    * a known enumeration.</li>
141    * <li>{@link java.lang.annotation.AnnotationTypeMismatchException}: An annotation property is not
142    * of the expected type.</li>
143    * </ul>
144    * Implementations of this interface must implement methods for {@link Object#hashCode()} and
145    * {@link Object#toString()} that resemble those used for the annotation values of an actual
146    * {@link java.lang.annotation.Annotation} implementation. Also, instances must implement
147    * {@link java.lang.Object#equals(Object)} to return {@code true} for other instances of
148    * this interface that represent the same annotation value.
149    *
150    * @param <U> The type of the loaded value of this annotation.
151    */
